maml:description.maml:para: A PowerShell function to establish a connection with Exchange Online.
This function is built using EWS Managed API and requires impersonation or minimum delegated permission. Contact Exchange Online administrator for more information.

maml:Description.maml:para: Exchange Online admin or any account with impersonation or delegate access permission on the mailbox.
Exchange Online admin or any account with impersonation or delegate access permission on the mailbox.

command:example.maml:title: Example 1
command:example.dev:code: PS C:\> Connect-xExchangeOnline -Credential 'admin@contoso.onmicrosoft.com'

dev:remarks.maml:para: This cmdlet is to connect with Exchange Online as administrator. Once the connection is established successfully other Exchange Online functions in this module re-use the same.

command:example.maml:title: Example 2
command:example.dev:code: PS C:\> $Credential = Get-Credential -Credential 'admin@contoso.onmicrosoft.com' PS C:\> Connect-xExchangeOnline -Credential $Credential

dev:remarks.maml:para: An alternate approach of Example 1 - Here the variable $Credential can be reused.

maml:description.maml:para: A PowerShell function to establish a connection with SharePoint Online tenant.

This PowerShell function is built using Client Side Object Model (CSOM). For a demo purpose we are connecting with SharePoint Online tenant as a tenant admin. So, we can access all other site collections and sites.

maml:Description.maml:para: SharePoint Online Tenant admin url (Example: https://tenant-admin.sharepoint.com)
SharePoint Online Tenant admin url (Example: https://tenant-admin.sharepoint.com)

command:example.maml:title: Example 1
command:example.dev:code: PS C:\> Connect-xSharePointOnline -Url 'https://contoso-admin.sharepoint.com' -Credential 'admin@contoso.onmicrosoft.com'

dev:remarks.maml:para: This cmdlet will allow you to establish a connection with SharePoint Online as tenant admin.

maml:description.maml:para: A PowerShell function to retrieve Junk email items from the given mailbox
This PowerShell function is built using EWS Managed API and requires impersonation permission or mailbox delegate permission.

maml:Description.maml:para: Number of junk email items to be retrieved - Default is 10
Number of junk email items to be retrieved - Default is 10

command:example.maml:title: Example 1
command:example.dev:code: PS C:\> Get-xJunkEmail -Identity 'user1@contoso.onmicrosoft.com'

dev:remarks.maml:para: Lists first 10 junk email items from the mailbox 'user1@contoso.onmicrosoft.com'

command:example.maml:title: Example 2
command:example.dev:code: PS C:\> 'user1@contoso.onmicrosoft.com' , 'user2@contoso.onmicrosoft.com' | Get-xJunkEmail

dev:remarks.maml:para: Lists first 10 junk email items from the mailbox 'user1@contoso.onmicrosoft.com' and 'user2@contoso.onmicrosoft.com'

command:example.maml:title: Example 3
command:example.dev:code: PS C:\> Get-xJunkEmail -Identity 'user1@contoso.onmicrosoft.com' -ItemCount 5

dev:remarks.maml:para: Lists first 5 junk email items from the mailbox 'user1@contoso.onmicrosoft.com'
